[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":657},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F09\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F09\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F09\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F09\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy\u002F":633,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F09\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy\u002F":642},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20201009\u002F3159624676\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":616,"date":617,"description":19,"extension":618,"lang":619,"meta":620,"navigation":621,"path":622,"readingMinutes":623,"seo":624,"standalone":625,"stem":626,"tags":627,"tldr":630,"updated":617,"url":631,"__hash__":632},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy.md","(26) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Tricks: Auto-Deploy with Travis CI","6764269513",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":605},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,35,38,47,50,60,64,67,70,77,91,126,129,147,150,156,159,162,165,181,184,187,190,195,198,205,210,213,217,220,226,229,235,246,251,254,260,263,277,283,286,290,297,302,305,533,540,545,549,552,558,568,577,580,598,601],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This kicks off a series of \"tricks\" (admittedly an odd term). First one is auto-deploy.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"auto-deploy","Auto-deploy",[17,25,26,27,31,32,34],{},"Normally after writing a post you run ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"hexo d -g"," to compile and push static pages to gh-pages. The compile process actually uses your machine's CPU — you've probably noticed your fans kicking up when running ",[28,33,30],{},".",[17,36,37],{},"The fix is to use CI\u002FCD. What's CI\u002FCD? Here's a great walkthrough from a community member (in Mandarin):",[17,39,40],{},[41,42,46],"a",{"href":43,"rel":44},"https:\u002F\u002Fithelp.ithome.com.tw\u002Farticles\u002F10219083",[45],"nofollow","Day12 What is CI\u002FCD (Mandarin)",[17,48,49],{},"Walking through CI\u002FCD theory isn't the point of this post — using it is. So this post covers two options:",[51,52,53,57],"ul",{},[54,55,56],"li",{},"Travis CI",[54,58,59],{},"GitHub Actions",[12,61,63],{"id":62},"uploading-the-hexo-project","Uploading the Hexo project",[17,65,66],{},"Before we set up Travis CI or GitHub Actions, we need to push the project to a remote repo, otherwise the rest of the steps won't work.",[17,68,69],{},"So first, create a remote repo just for Travis:",[17,71,72],{},[73,74],"img",{"alt":75,"src":76},"Public repo","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-14%2021.56.43.png",[17,78,79,80,84,85,90],{},"The first upload is straightforward. If you're not comfortable with git commands, revisit \"",[41,81,83],{"href":82},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F25\u002Flearn-hexo-12-basic-git-commands\u002F","(12) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Basic Git Commands You Can't Skip","\" or check out \"",[41,86,89],{"href":87,"rel":88},"https:\u002F\u002Fw3c.hexschool.com\u002Fgit\u002Fcfdbd310",[45],"Git & GitHub Tutorial Manual (Mandarin)","\". Here's the upload command just to keep things moving:",[92,93,98],"pre",{"className":94,"code":95,"language":96,"meta":97,"style":97},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git add .\ngit commit -m 'first'\ngit remote add origin https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fjc-eng\u002FTravis-hexo-project.git\ngit push -u origin master\n","cmd","",[28,99,100,108,114,120],{"__ignoreMap":97},[101,102,105],"span",{"class":103,"line":104},"line",1,[101,106,107],{},"git add .\n",[101,109,111],{"class":103,"line":110},2,[101,112,113],{},"git commit -m 'first'\n",[101,115,117],{"class":103,"line":116},3,[101,118,119],{},"git remote add origin https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fjc-eng\u002FTravis-hexo-project.git\n",[101,121,123],{"class":103,"line":122},4,[101,124,125],{},"git push -u origin master\n",[17,127,128],{},"For subsequent posts, just use:",[92,130,132],{"className":94,"code":131,"language":96,"meta":97,"style":97},"git add .\ngit commit -m 'first'\ngit push\n",[28,133,134,138,142],{"__ignoreMap":97},[101,135,136],{"class":103,"line":104},[101,137,107],{},[101,139,140],{"class":103,"line":110},[101,141,113],{},[101,143,144],{"class":103,"line":116},[101,145,146],{},"git push\n",[17,148,149],{},"Confirm your repo looks like this before moving on:",[17,151,152],{},[73,153],{"alt":154,"src":155},"Uploaded Hexo project","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-14%2022.02.52.png",[12,157,56],{"id":158},"travis-ci",[17,160,161],{},"Travis CI is well-known. We'll use Travis CI's CI (continuous integration) to auto-deploy to gh-pages. How does CI work? In short: when a user commits code to the remote repo, the CI system automatically runs tasks like testing, building, and deploying.",[17,163,164],{},"One thing to note when using Travis CI: it has two versions — the open-source one and the commercial one. The URL tells you which is which:",[51,166,167,174],{},[54,168,169,173],{},[41,170,171],{"href":171,"rel":172},"https:\u002F\u002Ftravis-ci.org\u002F",[45]," — open-source version",[54,175,176,180],{},[41,177,178],{"href":178,"rel":179},"https:\u002F\u002Ftravis-ci.com\u002F",[45]," — commercial version",[17,182,183],{},"What's the difference? Personally I'd recommend the open-source version — it's free.",[17,185,186],{},"The catch is your project has to be open source to use it. If your project is Private, you have to use the commercial version, which only gives you 100 free runs — after that you pay.",[17,188,189],{},"So I'll focus on the open-source version here.",[191,192,194],"h3",{"id":193},"travis-ci-open-source-version","Travis CI open-source version",[17,196,197],{},"You can sign into Travis CI with your GitHub account, so I'll skip the signup walkthrough.",[17,199,200,201,204],{},"After signing in, click ",[28,202,203],{},"setting"," from the top menu:",[17,206,207],{},[73,208],{"alt":203,"src":209},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002FRay_-_Profile_-_Travis_CI.png",[17,211,212],{},"Find the \"Travis-hexo-project\" repo we just created. If it doesn't show up, click \"Sync Account\" on the left to refresh. The point is to confirm Travis can see your project.",[12,214,216],{"id":215},"github-access-token","GitHub Access Token",[17,218,219],{},"Once Travis can see your project, head back to GitHub and go to the GitHub Access Token page. If you can't find it, here's the direct link:",[17,221,222],{},[41,223,216],{"href":224,"rel":225},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fsettings\u002Ftokens",[45],[17,227,228],{},"Click \"Generate new token\" at the top right:",[17,230,231],{},[73,232],{"alt":233,"src":234},"Generate new token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-16%2014.14.57.png",[17,236,237,238,241,242,245],{},"The name is whatever you want. The important part is checking ",[28,239,240],{},"public_repo"," under ",[28,243,244],{},"repo",". Scroll down and save to generate the token:",[17,247,248],{},[73,249],{"alt":240,"src":250},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-16%2014.17.55.png",[17,252,253],{},"After submit you'll get a token (inside the green box). Copy it (and don't leak it):",[17,255,256],{},[73,257],{"alt":258,"src":259},"token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F1600237180965.jpg",[17,261,262],{},"Back in Travis CI, open the settings for the project we created. There's an \"Environment Variables\" section — fill in:",[51,264,265,271],{},[54,266,267,268],{},"name: ",[28,269,270],{},"GITHUBHEXO_TOKEN",[54,272,273,274],{},"value: ",[28,275,276],{},"the token from above",[17,278,279],{},[73,280],{"alt":281,"src":282},"Environment Variables","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F1600237782375.jpg",[17,284,285],{},"Click Add.",[12,287,289],{"id":288},"creating-travisyml","Creating .travis.yml",[17,291,292,293,296],{},"The next step is important — we need to create the Travis CI config file. Travis CI runs everything based on this file (generating pages, installing the environment, etc.). Create a file called ",[28,294,295],{},".travis.yml"," in the root of your Hexo project (heads up, root directory):",[17,298,299],{},[73,300],{"alt":295,"src":301},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-16%2014.25.20.png",[17,303,304],{},"What goes inside? Here's a ready-to-use template:",[92,306,310],{"className":307,"code":308,"language":309,"meta":97,"style":97},"language-yml shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","# Set system language environment\nlanguage: node_js\n# Whether sudo is required\nsudo: false\n# Set node_js version\nnode_js:\n  - '12'\n# Cache directories\ncache:\n  apt: true\n  directories:\n      - node_modules # folder that doesn't change often\n# Branch to deploy from. Usually master. This tells Travis to run when this branch gets a commit\nbranches:\n  only:\n    - master\n## Install Hexo-Cli\nbefore_script:\n  - npm install hexo-cli -g  # install Hexo\n# Clean cache and compile\nscript:\n  - hexo clean\n  - hexo generate\n## Deploy config\nafter_success:\n  - sed -i'' \"\u002F^ *repo\u002Fs~github\\.com~${GITHUBHEXO_TOKEN}@github.com~\" _config.yml\n  - hexo deploy\n","yml",[28,311,312,318,332,337,348,354,363,372,378,386,397,405,417,423,431,439,448,454,462,473,479,487,495,503,509,517,525],{"__ignoreMap":97},[101,313,314],{"class":103,"line":104},[101,315,317],{"class":316},"sQrFR","# Set system language environment\n",[101,319,320,324,328],{"class":103,"line":110},[101,321,323],{"class":322},"sKpQp","language",[101,325,327],{"class":326},"sMAXC",": ",[101,329,331],{"class":330},"sTRMh","node_js\n",[101,333,334],{"class":103,"line":116},[101,335,336],{"class":316},"# Whether sudo is required\n",[101,338,339,342,344],{"class":103,"line":122},[101,340,341],{"class":322},"sudo",[101,343,327],{"class":326},[101,345,347],{"class":346},"sCcAr","false\n",[101,349,351],{"class":103,"line":350},5,[101,352,353],{"class":316},"# Set node_js version\n",[101,355,357,360],{"class":103,"line":356},6,[101,358,359],{"class":322},"node_js",[101,361,362],{"class":326},":\n",[101,364,366,369],{"class":103,"line":365},7,[101,367,368],{"class":326},"  - ",[101,370,371],{"class":330},"'12'\n",[101,373,375],{"class":103,"line":374},8,[101,376,377],{"class":316},"# Cache directories\n",[101,379,381,384],{"class":103,"line":380},9,[101,382,383],{"class":322},"cache",[101,385,362],{"class":326},[101,387,389,392,394],{"class":103,"line":388},10,[101,390,391],{"class":322},"  apt",[101,393,327],{"class":326},[101,395,396],{"class":346},"true\n",[101,398,400,403],{"class":103,"line":399},11,[101,401,402],{"class":322},"  directories",[101,404,362],{"class":326},[101,406,408,411,414],{"class":103,"line":407},12,[101,409,410],{"class":326},"      - ",[101,412,413],{"class":330},"node_modules",[101,415,416],{"class":316}," # folder that doesn't change often\n",[101,418,420],{"class":103,"line":419},13,[101,421,422],{"class":316},"# Branch to deploy from. Usually master. This tells Travis to run when this branch gets a commit\n",[101,424,426,429],{"class":103,"line":425},14,[101,427,428],{"class":322},"branches",[101,430,362],{"class":326},[101,432,434,437],{"class":103,"line":433},15,[101,435,436],{"class":322},"  only",[101,438,362],{"class":326},[101,440,442,445],{"class":103,"line":441},16,[101,443,444],{"class":326},"    - ",[101,446,447],{"class":330},"master\n",[101,449,451],{"class":103,"line":450},17,[101,452,453],{"class":316},"## Install Hexo-Cli\n",[101,455,457,460],{"class":103,"line":456},18,[101,458,459],{"class":322},"before_script",[101,461,362],{"class":326},[101,463,465,467,470],{"class":103,"line":464},19,[101,466,368],{"class":326},[101,468,469],{"class":330},"npm install hexo-cli -g",[101,471,472],{"class":316},"  # install Hexo\n",[101,474,476],{"class":103,"line":475},20,[101,477,478],{"class":316},"# Clean cache and compile\n",[101,480,482,485],{"class":103,"line":481},21,[101,483,484],{"class":322},"script",[101,486,362],{"class":326},[101,488,490,492],{"class":103,"line":489},22,[101,491,368],{"class":326},[101,493,494],{"class":330},"hexo clean\n",[101,496,498,500],{"class":103,"line":497},23,[101,499,368],{"class":326},[101,501,502],{"class":330},"hexo generate\n",[101,504,506],{"class":103,"line":505},24,[101,507,508],{"class":316},"## Deploy config\n",[101,510,512,515],{"class":103,"line":511},25,[101,513,514],{"class":322},"after_success",[101,516,362],{"class":326},[101,518,520,522],{"class":103,"line":519},26,[101,521,368],{"class":326},[101,523,524],{"class":330},"sed -i'' \"\u002F^ *repo\u002Fs~github\\.com~${GITHUBHEXO_TOKEN}@github.com~\" _config.yml\n",[101,526,528,530],{"class":103,"line":527},27,[101,529,368],{"class":326},[101,531,532],{"class":330},"hexo deploy\n",[17,534,535,536,539],{},"Now every time you push a new post to your Hexo project on GitHub (i.e. ",[28,537,538],{},"git push","), it'll auto-deploy.",[17,541,542],{},[73,543],{"alt":23,"src":544},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-16%2014.45.53.png",[12,546,548],{"id":547},"extra","Extra",[17,550,551],{},"If Travis CI just won't trigger, check your project's status in settings to see if it's enabled:",[17,553,554],{},[73,555],{"alt":556,"src":557},"Enabled status","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-09-16%2014.58.07.png",[17,559,560,561,564,565,567],{},"One last landmine that catches a lot of people. After enabling CI you might notice your theme stops rendering properly. Open the current theme folder in your Hexo project, enable hidden folder visibility, and delete the ",[28,562,563],{},".git"," folder inside the theme. Themes are cloned via git, so they have their own ",[28,566,563],{}," folder. Since you've already uploaded once, you'll need to re-stage the theme folder:",[92,569,571],{"className":94,"code":570,"language":96,"meta":97,"style":97},"git rm -r --cache themes\u002F\n",[28,572,573],{"__ignoreMap":97},[101,574,575],{"class":103,"line":104},[101,576,570],{},[17,578,579],{},"Then re-stage and push:",[92,581,583],{"className":94,"code":582,"language":96,"meta":97,"style":97},"git add .\ngit commit -m 'fix'\ngit push\n",[28,584,585,589,594],{"__ignoreMap":97},[101,586,587],{"class":103,"line":104},[101,588,107],{},[101,590,591],{"class":103,"line":110},[101,592,593],{},"git commit -m 'fix'\n",[101,595,596],{"class":103,"line":116},[101,597,146],{},[17,599,600],{},"And it should auto-deploy properly.",[602,603,604],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}",{"title":97,"searchDepth":110,"depth":110,"links":606},[607,608,609,610,613,614,615],{"id":14,"depth":110,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":110,"text":23},{"id":62,"depth":110,"text":63},{"id":158,"depth":110,"text":56,"children":611},[612],{"id":193,"depth":116,"text":194},{"id":215,"depth":110,"text":216},{"id":288,"depth":110,"text":289},{"id":547,"depth":110,"text":548},"Hexo","2020-10-09 00:01:00","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy","4",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy",[616,628,629,56],"Learning Hexo from Scratch","iThome Ironman 2020",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F09\u002Flearn-hexo-26-travis-ci-deploy\u002F","tWV6sPYJDLxxqguMtezDqxZyWcQLMR6ff0wqFUKTGek",{"newer":634,"older":638},{"url":635,"title":636,"date":637},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-hexo-27-github-actions-deploy\u002F","(27) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Tricks: Auto-Deploy with GitHub Actions","2020-10-10 00:00:01",{"url":639,"title":640,"date":641},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F08\u002Flearn-hexo-25-seo-extra-concepts\u002F","(25) Learning Hexo from Scratch - SEO: Extra Concepts","2020-10-08 00:01:00",[643,648,653],{"url":644,"title":645,"date":646,"readingMinutes":647},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F30\u002Ffix-hexo-updated-date-on-ci-deploy\u002F","Fix: All Posts Show Updated Date After Hexo Upgrade or CI Deploy","2022-10-30 11:52:35","2",{"url":649,"title":650,"date":651,"readingMinutes":652},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F11\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-33-updating-next-theme\u002F","(33) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Updating the NexT Theme","2020-11-01 13:21:00","3",{"url":654,"title":655,"date":656,"readingMinutes":647},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F31\u002Flearn-hexo-32-updating-hexo\u002F","(32) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Updating Hexo","2020-10-31 14:01:51",1784010275374]